# Tailwind CSS Guidelines

## Configuration
- Tailwind CSS v4 is configured in the project
- Custom CSS variables are defined in [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css)
- Use the `@/*` import alias for components

## Styling Approach
- Use utility-first approach with Tailwind classes
- Prefer Tailwind utilities over custom CSS
- Use responsive prefixes (sm:, md:, lg:, xl:) for responsive design
- Use dark: prefix for dark mode styles

## Color Scheme
- Primary colors: blue-600, purple-600 for gradients
- Background: slate-50 to slate-100 (light), slate-900 (dark)
- Text: slate-900 (light), white (dark)
- Use semantic color names: text-slate-600, bg-slate-50, etc.

## Component Styling
- Use consistent spacing with Tailwind's spacing scale
- Apply hover states with hover: prefix
- Use focus states for accessibility
- Implement proper contrast ratios

## Layout Patterns
- Use Flexbox and Grid utilities for layouts
- Container classes for max-width and centering
- Responsive grid: grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3
- Use gap utilities for spacing between elements

## Common Patterns
- Cards: bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 border rounded-lg shadow
- Buttons: Use Shadcn/UI Button component with variants
- Forms: Use consistent spacing and focus states
- Gradients: bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 to-purple-600

